transliteration: Ninand Get Briddayan|| Akhed Naad Duddharan||
translation: Thou art radiant like the great ball of the Sun; beyond the tunes of worldly joys.

transliteration: Athatt Batt Battakan|| Aghatt Anatt Soukkhalan||4||82||
translation: Thou art everlasting like the Bunyan-seed; and art Blissful ever perfectly.4.82.

transliteration: Akhoutt Toutt Dribbakan|| Ajoutt Chhoutt Souchchhakan||
translation: The Treasure of Thy wealth is inexhaustible; O Immaculate Lord! Thou art not united with anyone.

transliteration: Aghoutt Toutt Aasanan|| Alekh Abhekh Anaasanan||5||83||
translation: Thy seat is eternal; Thou art accountless, guiseless and Imperishable.5.83.

gurmukhi: suBMq dMq pdukM ]jlMq swm su GtM ]
transliteration: Soubhant Dant Padoukan|| Jalant Saam Su Ghataaag||
translation: The row of thy teeth looks graceful; seeing which the dark clouds feel jealous.

transliteration: Soubhant Chhudra Ghantakaa|| Jalant Bhaarak Chhataa||6||84||
translation: The small bells look elegant in the string round Thy waist; seeing Thy effulgence the splendour of the Sun feels jealous.6.84.

gurmukhi: isrI su sIs su`BIXM ]Gtwk bwn au`BIXM ]
transliteration: Sirisu Sees Soubbheeyan|| Ghatek Baan Oubbheeyan||
translation: The crest on Thy head seems splendid; like the shaft high up in the clouds.
The Crown on Thy head looks elegant; seeing which the moon feels shy.7.85.

gurmukhi: clMq dMq p`qkM ]BjMq dyiK du dlM ]
transliteration: Chalant Dant Pattakan|| Bhajant Dekh(i) Du Dalan||
translation: The rows of demons are moving; and both the armies are running.

gurmukhi: qjMq ssqR AsqRkM ]clMq c`kR cau idsM ]8]86]
transliteration: Tajant Sastra Astrakan|| Chalant Chakkra Chau Disan||8||86||
translation: When Thou usest Thy arms and weapons; and Thy disc moves in all the four directions.8.86.

transliteration: Agadm Tej Sobheeyan|| Rikhees Ees Lobheeyan||
translation: Thy Inaccesible Glory looks elegant; therefore the great sages and Shiva are covetous to have Thy Sight.

gurmukhi: Anyk bwr iDAwvhI ]n qqR pwr pwvhI ]9]87]
transliteration: Anek Baar Dhiaavahee|| Na Tatra Paar Paavahee||9||87||
translation: They remember Thy Name many times; even then they have not been able go know Thy limits.9.87.

gurmukhi: ADo su DUm DUm hI ]AGUr nyqR GUm hI ]
transliteration: Adho Su Dhoom Dhoom Hee|| Aghoor Netra Ghoom Hee||
translation: Many with faces upside down light the fire; many ascetics roam forsaking their sleep.

gurmukhi: su pMc Agn swDIXM ]n qwm pwr lwDIXM ]10]88]
transliteration: Su Panch Agad Saadheeyan|| Na Taam Paar Laadheeyan||10||88||
translation: Many perform austerity of five fires; even they have not been able to know thy limits.10.88.
